#Text=DS : Do you feel home up in Boston ?
#Text=AD : I do , and part of that is the great folk community .
#Text=DS : Why do you think Boston has such a well-developed folk scene ?
#Text=AD : It ’s always historically been a folk hub .
#Text=There ’s a lot of awesome folk stations like WUMB and WERS .
#Text=Legendary folk clubs , like Club Passim .
#Text=Those have stayed in tact since the sixties .
#Text=DS : Is there anything culturally about Boston that makes it more conducive to folk ?
#Text=AD : Once you have a buzz , the buzz creates more buzz .
#Text=Some people hear there ’s a folk scene in Boston , and then other people move there , so the scene feeds itself and becomes a successful scene .
#Text=It ’s on-going .
#Text=DS : Do you have a favorite curse word ?
#Text=AD : [ Giggles ] Cunt . [ Giggles ]
#Text=DS : Really ? !
#Text=You are the first woman I have met who likes that word !
#Text=AD : Oh , really ? I ’ll use it in a traffic situation .
#Text=Road rage . [ Laughs ]
#Text=DS : Do you find yourself more inspired by man-made creations , including people and ideas , or nature-made creations ?
#Text=AD : I love nature , but it is limited .
#Text=It is what it is , and does n’t include the human imagination that can go so much further than nature .
#Text=DS : What are some man made things that inspire you ?
#Text=AD : New York City as a whole is just an amazing city .
#Text=People are so creative and it is the hub of personal creativity , just in the way people express themselves on a daily basis .
#Text=DS : Do you think you will return ?
#Text=In theory I will return one day if I have money , but in theory you need money to enjoy yourself .
#Text=DS :
#Text=What trait do you deplore in yourself ?
#Text=AD : Like anyone , I think laziness .
#Text=I ’m a bit a hard on myself , but there ’s always more I can do .

#Text=As a touring singer-songwriter I work hard , but sometimes I forget because I get to sleep in and my job is not conventional , and sometimes I think ‘ Oh , I do n’t even have a job , how lazy I am ! ’ [ Laughs ]
#Text=Then , of course , there are times I ’m touring my ass off and I work hard as well .
#Text=It comes in shifts .
#Text=There are times there is so much free time I have to structure my own days , and that ’s a challenge .

#Text=DS : When is the last time you achieved a goal and were disappointed by it and thought , “ Is that all there is ? ” Something you wanted to obtain , you obtained it , and it was n’t nearly as fulfilling as you thought it would be .
#Text=AD : I was just thinking about the whole dream of becoming a musician .
#Text=I want to maybe do a research project about people ’s dreams and how they feel about them after they come true .
#Text=It ’s really interesting .
#Text=They change a lot .
#Text=When I was 17 I saw Ani Difranco on stage and I wanted to do that , and now I ’m doing it .
#Text=Now I think about Ani very differently .
#Text=I wonder how long it took her to drive here , she must be tired ; I ’m thinking of all the pragmatic things that go on behind the scenes .
#Text=The backside of a dream you never consider when you ’re dreaming it .
#Text=To some extent , having my dream fulfilled has n’t been a let-down , but it ’s changed .
#Text=It ’s more realistic .
